title: Santana Ultimate Collection (2007) 320k CD (musicfromrizzo)
description:
Carlos Santana has great human appeal in his gift of musical genius.
What beauty indeed there must be in what is his innermost spirit to produce what
he does to edify and cherish those around him all the way down there where he is.

Some of my favourite songs are done by him and his guests, including selections
on this CD such as "Samba pa ti", "Corazon espinado" (feat Mana), "Smooth" (feat. Rob Thomas)and I dearly love "The Game Of Love" (feat. Michelle Branch).

There's nice standard Santana older songs like Oye como va and Black magic woman
on here too.

Its better than the real "hard" rock and punk shit that's the stuff of seemingly
inhuman-like appeal that is consumed so much of out in western countries instead.

Santana's musical taste is certainly of superior european genius I figure,than whats around much of there rest of this planet too certainly, I believe - and he hasn't lost his touch in this regard by being elsewhere so long and being in the sun to the point of looking like a tourist in some western parts - its what is in his heart and soul that matters and his music is proof of that for the most part - and supremely so I believe. He is therefore a better man than are those seeking to tear down his image for not looking the part in the minds of all too many who cant come up with anything good in their minds instead by relative comparison of any merit whatever.

Thanks for seeding

Michael Rizzo Chessman
(musicfromrizzo)
